%S A394511 4,8,8,8,8,10,10,10,12,12,12,12,12,14,14,14,14,14,16,16
%N A394511 Minimum number of cells in a connected enclosing shell of an n-cell connected hole on the truncated-square (4.8.8) Archimedean tiling.
%C A394511 The 4.8.8 tiling is the Archimedean truncated square tiling: regular squares and regular octagons in a 1:1 ratio, symmetry group p4mm. An n-cell connected hole H is a connected set of n cells (squares or octagons). The corona C(H) is the set of cells edge-adjacent to H but not in H. An enclosing shell S is a connected superset of C(H), disjoint from H, such that the cells outside H union S also form a connected set. a(n) is the minimum |S| over all such (H, S).
%C A394511 Three conjectures hold for n = 1..20 (UNVERIFIED beyond): (C1) the minimum shell equals the corona, |S| = |C(H)|; (C2) a(n) is nondecreasing; (C3) a(n) - a(n - 1) is in {0, 2} for n >= 3.
%C A394511 For each n in 1..20, a(n) is sandwiched at value k. Upper bound: a Cython implementation of Redelmeier's polyform enumeration (within graph-distance 8 of an anchor cell) yields a witness with |S| = k. Lower bound: a PySAT CEGAR encoder produces a drat-trim-certified UNSAT proof at k - 1. A disjoint Python geometric verifier independently re-checks every witness.
%H A394511 Peter Exley, <a href="https://github.com/pexley-math/oeis-A394511">Solver code, data, and figures</a>, GitHub.
%e A394511 For n = 1, a(1) = 4: a single square cell as the hole has corona of size 4 (its four octagon neighbors), and that corona is connected and forms a valid enclosing shell.
%e A394511 For n = 2, a(2) = 8: every 2-cell connected hole on 4.8.8 contains at least one octagon; the corona of a square plus an adjacent octagon has 8 cells which form a connected ring around the hole.
%e A394511 For n = 5, a(5) = 8: the last n in the first plateau (a(n) = 8 for n = 2..5); adding interior cells to the hole does not enlarge the corona while the optimal shape stays compact.
%Y A394511 Cf. A182619 (analogous shell sequence on the regular hexagonal grid), A227004 (coordination sequence for the truncated-square 4.8.8 tiling; different "shell" concept, concentric coordination shells, included as disambiguation), A283056 (smallest polyomino admitting a hole of size n on the regular square grid).
